<collectingCountry id="ECE6FC97FFF3FFC0FEEDFF61FE617AF1" box="[372,436,227,250]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="ECE6FC97FFF3FFC0FE73FF61FD9C7AF1" box="[490,585,227,250]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(new record, Fig. 32). 
<collectingCountry id="ECE6FC97FFF3FFC0FCDCFF61FCB67AF1" box="[837,867,227,250]" name="American Samoa" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">As</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName id="53F1C784FFF3FFC0FCF2FF66FC387AF0" box="[875,1005,228,251]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sundaica">
<emphasis id="A6856015FFF3FFC0FCF2FF66FC387AF0" box="[875,1005,228,251]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">H. sundaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species is apparently widely distributed. It was described from 
<collectingCountry id="ECE6FC97FFF3FFC0FCADFE81FCA17B11" box="[820,884,259,282]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and, as the first new record since its original description, is here documented from a forest in northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="ECE6FC97FFF3FFC0FF43FEC1FEE97B51" box="[218,316,323,346]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="213">Thailand</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
